<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="reward-vt">reward <strong><em>vt</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /rɪ'wɔːd/    美 /rɪ'wɔːrd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>[常用于被动语态] 报答；酬劳；奖赏：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The police will reward whoever provides useful information to catch the robber.
任何人提供有用信息帮助抓住劫匪，警方将予以奖励。</p><footer>2014 湖北</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The students have been working hard on their lessons and their efforts will be <strong>rewarded with</strong> success in the end.
学生们一直努力学习功课，他们的努力最终会带来成功。</p><footer>2016 北京</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>rewarding /rɪ'wɔːdɪŋ/ adj   </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>When asked for his views about his teaching job, Philip said he found it very interesting and rewarding. 
当被问及对教学工作的看法时，菲利普说它既有趣又有意义。</p><footer>2012 安徽</footer></div></div>